{"questionId":"11819","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This question will investigate the solution to a coupled system of differential equations and how to transform it to a system that can be solved by the eigenvector method.</p>\n<p>It is desired to solve the coupled system of differential equations</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\dot x = x + 2y - 50\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>50</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\dot y = 2x + y - 40\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>40</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;represent the population of two types of symbiotic coral and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is time measured in decades.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>If initially <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 100\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>100</mn>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = 50\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>50</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;use Euler’s method with an time increment of 0.1 to find an approximation for the values of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span> when&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t = 1\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Using <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {{x_{n + 1}} = {x_n} + 0.1\\left( {{x_n} + 2{y_n} - 50} \\right)} \\\\   {{y_{n + 1}} = {y_n} + 0.1\\left( {2{x_n} + {y_n} - 40} \\right)} \\\\   {{t_{n + 1}} = {t_n} + 0.1}  \\end{array}\">\n  <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mrow>\n                <mi>n</mi>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mi>n</mi>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>0.1</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <mrow>\n                <msub>\n                  <mi>x</mi>\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </msub>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n              <mrow>\n                <msub>\n                  <mi>y</mi>\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </msub>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>50</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>y</mi>\n              <mrow>\n                <mi>n</mi>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>y</mi>\n              <mi>n</mi>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>0.1</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n              <mrow>\n                <msub>\n                  <mi>x</mi>\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </msub>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mrow>\n                <msub>\n                  <mi>y</mi>\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </msub>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>40</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mrow>\n                <mi>n</mi>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mi>n</mi>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>0.1</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n  </mtable>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>Gives&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\\left( 1 \\right) \\simeq 848{\\text{,}}\\,\\,y\\left( 1 \\right) \\simeq 837\\,\\left( {3sf} \\right)\\,\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>≃</mo>\n  <mn>848</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>≃</mo>\n  <mn>837</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mi>s</mi>\n      <mi>f</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; M1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11819","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.3b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"If initially x = 100 and y = 50 use Euler’s method with an time increment of 0.1 to find an approximation for the values of x and y when t = 1 .","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.17—Phase portrait"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}